<p>Adjectives are declinable in similar way.</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Old_Persian_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Verbs">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Verbs">Verbs</span></h3>
<p><b>Voices</b><br />
Active, Middle (them. pres. -<b>aiy-</b>, -<b>ataiy-</b>), Passive (-<b>ya-</b>).</p>
<p>Mostly the forms of first and third persons are attested. The only preserved Dual form is <i>ajīva<b>tam</b></i> 'both lived'.</p>
